{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566560","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566560"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18843"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18843","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18843"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.12,0.82,0.01,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11576"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"94875"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11576","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11576"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18843"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"77882"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11297"},{"type":"tags","id":"11300"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27245"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27258"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31831"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32549"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32550"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32551"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"94875","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/94875"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA General Practitioner decides they can no longer provide care to a patient due to developing a personal relationship with the patient\u0027s family member. The practitioner recognises this creates a conflict of interest that could compromise professional judgment.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in managing this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document concerns in electronic medical record only","Send written notification advising care will be transferred to a colleague","Arrange to meet with the patient to discuss transfer of care and explain reasons","Immediately cease all contact with the patient","Ask the practice receptionist to phone the patient to advise of the need to transfer care"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Earrange to meet with the patient to discuss transfer of care and explain reasons\u003C/strong\u003E. This maintains clear professional boundaries while ensuring continuity of care. The doctor should communicate the decision professionally, explaining that a conflict of interest has arisen without sharing excessive personal details. This approach respects the patient\u0027s right to information while maintaining appropriate confidentiality.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument concerns in electronic medical record only\u003C/strong\u003E - While documentation is important, this alone is insufficient and fails to address the conflict of interest or ensure ongoing patient care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESend written notification advising care will be transferred to a colleague\u003C/strong\u003E - Written notification alone is impersonal and may leave the patient feeling abandoned without adequate explanation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmediately cease all contact with the patient\u003C/strong\u003E - This represents patient abandonment and breaches professional obligations to ensure continuity of care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAsk the practice receptionist to phone the patient to advise of the need to transfer care\u003C/strong\u003E - Delegating this sensitive communication to non-clinical staff is inappropriate and fails to fulfill the doctor\u0027s professional responsibility to the patient\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen ending a therapeutic relationship, doctors must maintain clear professional boundaries while ensuring the patient receives appropriate ongoing care. This includes providing adequate notice of the transfer, arranging handover of clinical information, and communicating the decision professionally while protecting personal privacy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["When ending a therapeutic relationship, doctors must ensure patients are informed of the decision and reasons in a professional manner.","Doctors have an ethical obligation to facilitate ongoing care arrangements when ending a therapeutic relationship.","Clinical handover of relevant information is essential when transferring care to another provider."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"77882"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18843"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"77882","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/77882"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-25T21:25:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-25T21:28:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11576"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"94875"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"t